comment:
* Holds the result from a PIN attempt.
 *
 * @see TelephonyManager#supplyIccLockPin
 * @see TelephonyManager#supplyIccLockPuk
 * @see TelephonyManager#setIccLockEnabled
 * @see TelephonyManager#changeIccLockPin
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: PIN_RESULT_TYPE_SUCCESS
variables.comment: * Indicates that the pin attempt was a success.

variables.name: PIN_RESULT_TYPE_INCORRECT
variables.comment: * Indicates that the pin attempt was incorrect.

variables.name: PIN_RESULT_TYPE_FAILURE
variables.comment: * Indicates that the pin attempt was a failure.

variables.name: PIN_RESULT_TYPE_ABORTED
variables.comment: * Indicates that the pin attempt was aborted.

methods.name: public int getResult()
methods.comment:
* Returns the result of the PIN attempt.
     *
     * @return The result of the PIN attempt.

methods.name: public int getAttemptsRemaining()
methods.comment:
* Returns the number of PIN attempts remaining.
     * This will be set when {@link #getResult} is {@link #PIN_RESULT_TYPE_INCORRECT}.
     * Indicates the number of attempts at entering the PIN before the SIM will be locked and
     * require a PUK unlock to be performed.
     *
     * @return Number of attempts remaining.

methods.name: public static PinResult getDefaultFailedResult()
methods.comment:
* Used to indicate a failed PIN attempt result.
     *
     * @return default PinResult for failure.
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public String toString()
methods.comment: * String representation of the Pin Result.

methods.name: public int describeContents()
methods.comment: * Describe the contents of this object.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)
methods.comment: * Write this object to a Parcel.

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)
